name: Out Among The Stars
author: Merle Haggard
lyrics:
It's midnight at a liquor store in Texas
Beneath the neon, close up has just begun.
When a boy walks in the door and points a pistol
He can't find a job with man but he has found a gun
Well he pulls it off, no trace of confrontation
He let the old man run out in the street.
But he knows soon they come, guns blazing
And all ready he can feel that great relief.
Oh how many travelers get weary
Bearing both their burdens and their scars
Don't you think they'd love to stop complaining
and fly like eagles out among the stars.
He pictures the arrival of their consternation
Sees that old familiar anger in their tears
He knows as they pull their guns and shoot this loser
They'll be aiming at the demon in their eyes.
Oh how many travelers get weary
Bearing both their burdens and their scars
Don't you think they'd love to stop complaining
And fly like eagles out among the stars

Oh how many travelers get weary
Bearing both their burdens and their scars
Don't you think they'd love to stop complaining
and fly like eagles out among the stars  and
fly like eagles out among
the        stars.

 For the man that's gone.

'Cause it's a sad day in Floyd County Mr. Jones,

 For the man that's gone.

'Cause its a sad day in Floyd County, Mr. Jones.

'Cause it's a sad day in Floyd County Mr. Jones,
Yeah the grief is strong,
